      <p>
        So the points do indeed connect into a circle.  Let's convert the equation to rectangular form to see if we can figure out why.  We'll begin our exploration by first multiplying both sides of the equation <m>r=4\cos(\theta)</m> by <m>r</m>.  The reason for doing so will be easier to explain once we've done it, so let's get to it.
        <me>r \cdot r=r \cdot 4\cos(\theta)\,\,\Longrightarrow\,\,r^2=4r\cos(\theta)</me>
      </p>

